      "properties": {
        "caveat": {
          "const": "Counts are distinct 2020 FARS fatal crashes with at least one person in the involved mode, counted at most once per crash per mode. They are fatal-crash burden context, not exposure-normalized risk, incidence, causation, nonfatal crashes, near misses, record linkage, outcome validation, or a safety ranking. Mode cells overlap and are non-additive. A suppressed_or_zero cell combines a true zero with a positive count below k=10 and must never be read as zero. k=10 is a stability and publication guard for already-public FARS data, not a confidentiality guarantee. The official 2020 National archive covers the 50 states and District of Columbia; Puerto Rico requires a separately verified source."
        },
        "dataset_year": {
          "const": 2020
